<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="364" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,764,660,955]" pageId="5" pageNumber="364">
This species was not previously recorded from Mt 
<collectingRegion box="[197,281,694,720]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="5" pageNumber="364">Nimba</collectingRegion>
. This species was only captured within old growth or secondary forest at relatively low altitudes on both Liberian and Guinean sides of the mountain between 
<quantity box="[447,531,795,821]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="364" unit="m" value="450.0">450 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[608,692,795,821]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="364" unit="m" value="690.0">690 m</quantity>
a.s.l. We follow Nesi 
<emphasis box="[362,420,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="364">et al</emphasis>
. (2013) in recognising this newly described West African taxon as a species separate from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pagenstecher" authorityYear="1885" box="[324,498,896,922]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Megaloglossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="364" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="woermanni">
<emphasis box="[324,498,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="364">M. woermanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs further east.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
